  "text": "This audit identifies all Go source files in kubernetes/kubernetes that define the set of allowed RBAC verbs and validate that API handlers enforce these verb constraints.\n\n## Verb Definition and Constants\n\nThe standard Kubernetes RBAC verbs are defined in multiple locations:\n\n1. **Core Verb Constants** (plugin/pkg/auth/authorizer/rbac/bootstrappolicy/policy.go, lines 37-40):\n   - `Read = []string{\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"}`\n   - `Write = []string{\"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\", \"deletecollection\"}`\n   - `ReadWrite = []string{\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\", \"deletecollection\"}`\n   - `ReadUpdate = []string{\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"update\", \"patch\"}`\n\n2. **Flow Control Supported Verbs** (pkg/apis/flowcontrol/validation/validation.go, lines 50-60):\n   - Defines `supportedVerbs` set containing: \"get\", \"list\", \"create\", \"update\", \"delete\", \"deletecollection\", \"patch\", \"watch\", \"proxy\"\n\n3. **ABAC Verbs** (pkg/auth/authorizer/abac/abac.go, lines 274-279):\n   - Read-only policies use: \"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"\n   - Read-write policies use: \"*\"\n\n## Verb Enforcement in Authorization\n\nVerb constraints are enforced at multiple layers:\n\n1. **RBAC Authorizer** (plugin/pkg/auth/authorizer/rbac/rbac.go):\n   - `RuleAllows()` function (lines 168-176) checks if a request matches any rule\n   - Uses `VerbMatches()` to validate requested verb against rule verbs\n\n2. **Evaluation Helpers** (pkg/apis/rbac/v1/evaluation_helpers.go):\n   - `VerbMatches()` function (lines 26-37) implements verb matching logic\n   - Checks if rule verb is VerbAll (\"*\") or matches requested verb exactly\n   - Also implements `APIGroupMatches()`, `ResourceMatches()`, `ResourceNameMatches()`, `NonResourceURLMatches()`\n\n3. **Node Authorizer** (plugin/pkg/auth/authorizer/node/node_authorizer.go):\n   - `authorizeReadNamespacedObject()` (lines 196-214): enforces \"get\", \"list\", \"watch\" verbs only\n   - `authorizeLease()` (lines 260-286): enforces \"get\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\" verbs (line 264)\n   - `authorizeCSINode()` (lines 289-314): enforces \"get\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\" verbs (line 293)\n   - `authorizeResourceSlice()` (lines 317-360): enforces \"create\", \"get\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\", \"watch\", \"list\", \"deletecollection\" verbs (lines 325-336)\n   - `authorizeStatusUpdate()` (lines 164-179): enforces \"update\", \"patch\" verbs only\n   - `authorizeGet()` (lines 182-192): enforces \"get\" verb only\n   - `authorizeCreateToken()` (lines 236-257): enforces \"create\" verb only\n\n## Verb Validation and Policy Building\n\n1. **PolicyRuleBuilder Validation** (pkg/apis/rbac/helpers.go, lines 169-207):\n   - `Rule()` method validates that resource names cannot be used with \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", or \"deletecollection\" verbs (lines 189-200)\n   - Similar validation in pkg/apis/rbac/v1/helpers.go (lines 72-99)\n\n2. **Bootstrap Policies** (plugin/pkg/auth/authorizer/rbac/bootstrappolicy/controller_policy.go):\n   - Defines controller policies using `NewRule()` with specific verbs\n   - Includes special verbs: \"escalate\" (line 88), \"impersonate\" (policy.go line 314), \"approve\" (controller_policy.go), \"bind\" (policy.go)\n   - Examples of verb combinations across different controller roles and resources\n\n3. **Policy Validation** (pkg/apis/rbac/validation/validation.go):\n   - `ValidatePolicyRule()` ensures verbs are not empty (lines 105-107)\n\n4. **Policy Compaction** (pkg/registry/rbac/validation/policy_compact.go):\n   - `CompactRules()` function consolidates multiple rules with identical resources but different verbs\n\n## API Handler Verb Enforcement Chain\n\nThe authorization chain for verb enforcement:\n\n1. API request arrives with a verb\n2. `RBACAuthorizer.Authorize()` is called (plugin/pkg/auth/authorizer/rbac/rbac.go line 75)\n3. Calls `RuleAllows()` which invokes `VerbMatches()` for each applicable policy rule\n4. For node requests, `NodeAuthorizer.Authorize()` is called with specific verb enforcement in specialized methods\n5. Specialized authorizers (Node, ABAC) enforce verb constraints through switch statements or function calls\n\n## Key Verb Coverage Findings\n\nThe audit identifies complete verb coverage across the codebase:\n\n- **Standard Resource Verbs**: get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete, deletecollection\n- **Non-Resource Verbs**: proxy, and custom verbs like escalate, impersonate, approve, bind\n- **Verb Matching Logic**: Implemented through `VerbMatches()` function that supports wildcard matching\n- **Specialized Enforcement**: Node authorizer provides fine-grained control with specific verb validation for leases, CSINodes, ResourceSlices, and status subresources\n- **Bootstrap Policies**: All controller roles and cluster roles are constructed using verb constants, ensuring consistency\n\nAll API handlers enforce verb constraints through the RBAC/Node authorizer chain, with additional validation at policy creation time through PolicyRuleBuilder validation."
